            . I am a <rs id="t18190217-70-viclabel418" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190217-70-victim720 t18190217-70-viclabel418"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18190217-70-crimeloc419">Red Lion-street, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-70-crimeloc419" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-street, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-70-crimeloc419" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190217-70-off416 t18190217-70-crimeloc419"></join>. On the 13th of February, the prisoner came to the shop, about ten o'clock in the morning, while I was busy. He tried on several pair, but bought none; after he was gone I missed two odd shoes - he came again in about two hours, I set my boy to watch him; he said he was putting a shoe in his pocket; he immediately took a pair out. I found the two odd shoes I missed before in his bundle.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190217-70-person722">
                  GEORGE 
                  GREVEY
               <interp inst="t18190217-70-person722" type="surname" value="GREVEY"></interp>
